## LEARNINGS
- Touch events conflict with browser navigation/scroll on mobile — canvas panning must
  stand down while the user is scrolling; be careful with preventDefault in useCanvasEvents.
- All navigation flows through updateCurrentSection in useSectionManagement — the single
  integration point for any tracking or navigation feature.
- Voice is the product: specific first-person copy ("Tall skinny fat, slight athletic",
  the Now section) is what works; template phrasing reads as Lovable boilerplate.
  Full critiques: dev/research/23May26_claude_idea.md and 23May26_gemini_ideas.txt.
- Axis mental model for future sections: professional content on the horizontal axis,
  personal on the vertical. Don't rearrange existing sections; apply when adding new ones.
- Adding a section takes FOUR registration points: useSectionManagement's array,
  an App.tsx route above the catch-all, InfiniteCanvas's validSections list, and
  NavigationBreadcrumb's sectionNames map. Missing the route or validSections fails
  silently at build time and 404s at runtime — verify in a browser
  (.claude/skills/verify/SKILL.md has the recipe).

